<subSubSection id="C323E6F3FFBCD67FE5B1F9B5FF28FF6A" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="168" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B86B578FFBCD67EE5B1F9B5FDC1F897" blockId="16.[151,1437,1663,2014]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBCD67EE5B1F9B5FED0F927" bold="true" box="[151,274,1663,1690]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wing length 
<quantity id="4CC1189DFFBCD67EE48DF9B5FDE2F927" box="[427,544,1663,1690]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
. Fronto-orbital plate predominantly yellowish, darkened to upper fronto-orbital seta; face black in upper half, yellowish below; pedicel brown; legs brown; calypter yellowish, fringe yellowish. Aedeagus (Fig. 878 and 
<quantity id="4CC1189DFFBCD67EE48CF902FE33F95F" box="[426,497,1736,1762]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.23266" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" unit="in" value="879.0">879 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA8C889FFBCD67EE4DEF902FCD8F95F" author="Spencer, K. A. &amp; Steyskal, G. C." box="[504,794,1735,1762]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" refId="ref21231" refString="Spencer, K. A. &amp; Steyskal, G. C. (1986) Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. Department of Agriculture, Agriculture Handbook, 638. U. S. Dept. of Agriculture, Agricultural Research Service, Washington, D. C., 478 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 119606" type="book" year="1986">Spencer &amp; Steyskal 1986</bibRefCitation>
): basiphallus slightly sclerotized; mesophallus elongated, wider basally; reniform sclerite present between mesophallus and distiphallus; distiphallus short, forming two lobes and with paired distal processes.
</paragraph>
