<subSubSection id="C323E6F3FFBDD67FE5E1FEBAFEBAFD3A" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B86B578FFBDD67FE5E1FEBAFEBAFD3A" blockId="17.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE5E1FEBAFE8DFE36" bold="true" box="[199,335,368,395]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE47EFEBBFD9FFE36" authorityName=", Spencer" authorityYear="1981" box="[344,605,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyptera">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE47EFEBBFD9FFE36" box="[344,605,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Calycomyza platyptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has already been associated to 19 genera of host-plants belonging to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE5B1FE5FFED0FE12" box="[151,274,405,431]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
family (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA8C889FFBDD67FE457FE5FFD67FE12" author="Benavent-Corai, J. &amp; Martinez, M. &amp; Jimenez Peydro, R." box="[369,677,404,431]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 97" refId="ref18038" refString="Benavent-Corai, J. Martinez, M. &amp; Jimenez Peydro, R. (2005) Catalogue of the host plants of the world Agromyzidae (Diptera). Bollettino di Zoologica Agraria e di Bachicoltura, Series II, 37, 1 - 97." type="journal article" year="2005">
Benavent-Corai 
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE70DFE5CFDA1FE12" box="[555,611,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA8C889FFBDD67FE797FE5FFC1DFE12" author="Eiseman, C. S. &amp; Lonsdale, O." box="[689,991,405,431]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 156" refId="ref18711" refString="Eiseman, C. S. &amp; Lonsdale, O. (2018) New state and host records for Agromyzidae (Diptera) in the United States, with the description of thirty new species. Zootaxa, 4479 (1), 1 - 156. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4479.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Eiseman &amp; Lonsdale 2018</bibRefCitation>
), forming blotches on the surface of the leaf. The yellowish fronto-orbital plate, white calypter and fringe, legs completely brown and the tubular aedeagus are helpful to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE495FE17FD85FE4A" authorityName=", Spencer" authorityYear="1981" box="[435,583,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyptera">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE495FE17FD85FE4A" box="[435,583,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">C. platyptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from many others species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE6A9FE17FBDAFE4A" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1931" box="[911,1048,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE6A9FE17FBDAFE4A" box="[911,1048,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Calycomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Among species of this genus with a tubular aedeagus, especially that mining 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE749FDCBFD2FFDA6" box="[623,749,513,539]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE7D1FDCBFC48FDA6" authorityName=", Spencer" authorityYear="1981" box="[759,906,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyptera">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE7D1FDCBFC48FDA6" box="[759,906,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">C. platyptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an aedeagus similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE19DFDCBFA5AFDA6" authority="Spencer" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1973" box="[1211,1432,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE19DFDCBFAF7FDA6" box="[1211,1333,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">C. obscura</emphasis>
Spencer
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE5B1FDEFFEB4FDFD" authority="(Frick)" authorityName="Frick" baseAuthorityName="Frick" box="[151,374,549,576]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="promissa">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE5B1FDEFFEDCFD82" box="[151,286,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">C. promissa</emphasis>
(Frick)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE4A4FDEFFD99FD82" authority="(Spencer)" authorityName="Spencer" baseAuthorityName="Spencer" box="[386,603,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE4A4FDEFFE24FD82" box="[386,486,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">C. minor</emphasis>
(Spencer)
</taxonomicName>
e 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE750FDEFFC6DFDFD" authority="(Kaltenbach)" authorityName="Kaltenbach" baseAuthorityName="Kaltenbach" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[630,943,549,576]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solidaginis">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE750FDEFFCD1FD82" box="[630,787,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">C. solidaginis</emphasis>
(Kaltenbach)
</taxonomicName>
, distinguished by the sclerotized extensions present apically in the distiphallus. This set of characteristics are useful to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE142FD83FB19FDDE" box="[1124,1243,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="playtera">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE142FD83FB19FDDE" box="[1124,1243,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">C playtera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from others species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C39CEFBFFBDD67FE5CEFDA7FEB3FD3A" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1931" box="[232,369,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94D696AFFBDD67FE5CEFDA7FEB3FD3A" box="[232,369,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Calycomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
